This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a new architecture for image recognition tasks. Additionally, the paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art performance on the MNIST dataset, which is a commonly used dataset for image recognition tasks. 

The paper also involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning techniques (cs.LG) to train the capsule system. 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the use of discriminative training (cs.AI) and iterative routing-by-agreement mechanisms (cs.CL) to improve the performance of the capsule system.
